Output Parser for GENIE3

genie.Rd

This function parses the standard output generated by the BEELINE tool GENIE3.

genie(file_path)

Arguments

file_path

a file path to the GENIE3 output file generated by BEELINE.

Author

Sergio Vasquez and Hajk-Georg Drost

Examples

# path to GENIE3 output file
genie3_output <- system.file('beeline_examples/GENIE3/outFile.csv', package = 'scNetworkR')
# import GENIE3 specific output
genie3_parsed <- genie(genie3_output)
# look at output
head(genie3_parsed)
